  "prompt": "Why is the corner of my eye soring?",
  "response": "Pain or discomfort in the corner of the eye can be caused by various factors. Here are some common possibilities:\n\n1. **Eye Strain**: Prolonged use of screens, reading, or other activities that require intense focus can cause eye strain and discomfort, including in the corner of the eye.\n\n2. **Dry Eyes**: Reduced tear production or poor tear quality can lead to dry spots on the eye surface, causing soreness and irritation.\n\n3. **Allergies**: Allergic reactions to pollen, dust, pet dander, or other allergens can cause itching, redness, and soreness in and around the eyes.\n\n4. **Infections**: Bacterial or viral infections, such as conjunctivitis (pink eye), can lead to soreness, redness, and discharge.\n\n5. **Blocked Tear Ducts**: A blockage in the tear ducts can result in pain and swelling in the corner of the eye.\n\n6. **Foreign Bodies**: Small particles like dust, dirt, or an eyelash can get lodged in the corner of the eye, causing pain and irritation.\n\n7. **Styes**: A stye is a painful, red bump near the edge of the eyelid which can cause soreness in the corner of the eye.\n\nIf your symptoms persist or worsen, it\u2019s advisable to consult a healthcare professional for an accurate diagnosis and appropriate treatment.",
